TextChange: A saying, that I am not sure when it was created or if it really is a saying, goes \"If it wasn't on Instagram, it didn't happen.\" People have now become defined by what they see on television or social media. Therefore, the deluge of images and impressions we receive from local news, social media and the 24-hour news channels, has absolutely had an effect on people, so much so that people basically believe anything that appears on them.\n\nBefore social media, most of the world was separated, only interacting once in a while. Nowadays, people can talk to anyone across the world. This type of information transmission has made it so if anything happens in the world, everyone will know about it in an instance. However, this has another consequence where any information that goes out could be wholly unreliable. This will lead to a ton of misinformation spreading before any truth can be established, thereby leading to a skewed reality for whoever sees the information. By the time the truth is uncovered, people who have seen the initial information will be skeptical and do not have any idea what to believe in
